{{Orphan|date=February 2009}} '''Claude E. McKinney''' (June 9, 1929, in [[Greensboro, North Carolina]] – November 11, 2008, in [[Raleigh, North Carolina]])<ref name="ncsu">David Hunt, [http://news.ncsu.edu/releases/219/ "Visionary Centennial Campus Planner Dies"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131020132933/http://news.ncsu.edu/releases/219/ |date=2013-10-20 }}, NC State University News Services, 12 November 2008, accessed 2008-11-13</ref> was a chief contributor to the design of [[Research Triangle Park]] and was dean of the [[North Carolina State University]] School of Design from 1973 to 1988.<ref name="ncsu" /> He was also the planner and director of the University's [[North Carolina State University Centennial Campus|Centennial Campus]].<ref name="ncsu" /> He died from [[Progressive supranuclear palsy]]
==Education== McKinney graduated with honours from Pfeiffer Junior College (now [[Pfeiffer University]]) in [[Misenheimer, North Carolina]].<ref name="obit">Jay Price, [http://www.newsobserver.com/news/v-print/story/1291267.html "N.C. visionary McKinney dies at 79"], Raleigh ''News & Observer'', 12 November 2008, accessed 2008-11-13</ref> In 1951 he graduated from the [[University of North Carolina]] with a degree in painting and design, later doing graduate work in the same subjects at UNC.<ref name="obit" />
