'''Marie-Chantal Croft''' (ca 1970) is an architect in [[Quebec]], Canada. She teaches architectural design at the School of Architecture of Laval University.<ref name=laval>{{cite web |url=https://www.arc.ulaval.ca/actualites/confrence-la-bibliothque-de-charlesbourg-du-concept-au-dtail.html |title=Marie-Chantale Croft présente: " La bibliothèque de Charlesbourg, du concept au détail. " |language=fr |publisher=Université Laval}}</ref>


==Biography==

She graduated from  [[Laval University]] in 1992.
She was a co-founder of the firm ''"Croft Pelletier"'' architectes in 1995 together with [[Patkau Architects]]. ''"Croft Pelletier"'' architectes designed the [[Grande Bibliothèque]] in [[Montreal]].<ref name=diplome>{{cite web |url=http://www.scom.ulaval.ca/contact/hiver02/09.html |title=À l'assaut de la Grande Bibliothèque du Québec |publisher=L'Association des diplômés de l'Université Laval |language=fr}}</ref> The firm also won the competition to design a major expansion to the bibliothèque de Charlesbourg in [[Charlesbourg, Quebec City|Quebec City]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.canadianarchitect.com/features/between-the-lines/ |title=Between the Lines |work=The National Review of Design and Practice |publisher=Royal Architectural Institute of Canada}}</ref> and received the Henry Adams Certificate of the [[American Institute of Architecture]].<ref name=diplome/> 

==Awards==

Croft has received the  Ronald J. Thom Award from the [[Canada Council for the Arts]], the {{Interlanguage link multi|Médaille Raymond-Blais|fr}}<ref name=laval/> and the Prix Marcel-Parizeau from the [[Ordre des architectes du Québec]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.quebecurbain.qc.ca/2005/09/19/une-firme-de-quebec-remporte-un-prix-prestigieux-en-architecture/ |title=Une firme de Québec remporte un prix prestigieux en architecture |work=Québec Urbain |language=fr |date=September 19, 2005}}</ref>

