'''Moodlerooms''' is an [[Open-source software|open source]] [[E-learning (theory)|eLearning]] company based in [[Baltimore]], [[Maryland]] and is the largest{{cn|date=October 2016}} provider of [[Moodle]] (Modular Object-Oriented Dynamic Learning Environment).<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.moodle.com|title=Moodle • Open Source Software for Online Learning|website=Moodle.com|language=en-US|access-date=2016-10-09}}</ref> 

Moodlerooms has supported [[Moodle]] software since 2005.  Moodlerooms offers a cloud hosted enterprise Moodle platform   [[Blackboard Inc.|Blackboard]], Inc merged with Moodlerooms and another certified [[Moodle]] Partner in Australia called NetSpot in April 2012. Moodlerooms remains an independent division within the Blackboard family of educational tools. 

